TUTORIAL 1

This is the picture that I start out with. I shrunk it down to fit the 100x100. The first thing I did was clean up Misty's shirt. Since it's all scratchy and ..liney.. in the manga, it'll make the coloring come up terribly. So here it is whitened.. Next I duplicate it and set that layer to color burn, opacity 40%. To make it darker. Next I take this brush & set it to Darken, 15% opacity. And then I erased everything covering Misty with the lasso tool. The I use this color F290A5 and color in the background at Multiply, 15% opacity. - Then I use a brush on 3[or 5] px in this color FFF86C, and color in her shirt on Multiply. I duplicate this and set it to Multiply, 20% opacity. Then I find a yellow that is particularly Pikachu'ish and color him in <3 *hugs him* Then I finish coloring Pikachu & do Misty's skin.For the skin I usually just go with a F5C795 & play around with the opacity. Now.. usually when you color in something that's black, it's not going to show up =/ so at first it seemed pointless to color in her hair.. but what the hey! So I made her a little wig & set it to soft light, opacity 60%. Believe it or not.. those are Misty's EYEBALLS! :O :O :O I SWIPED 'EM! .........So I draw 2 blue dottish things & set them to Color Dodge, 60% opacity. Lastly I added a few brushes by And the voi la! here we are - <3 I hope this tutorial isn't completely useless! lol! These are some other icons I've made using this kind of method. If you use any of these, please credit me,
------------ Going from to !

TUTORIAL 2

Start off with this tex by [that I altered for this icon] as your background. Next, take this brush by and set it to Color Burn, opacity 10%. Next get three [or more] pictures of your fandom [or whatever you're making this icon of.] I'm choosing Poke'mon, one of my old obsessions <3 this episode is still a classic, battle aboard the St. Anne. So I take James and I shrink all 3 pictures down to [width] 34 by [height] 60. And then smush them together. Then I place it in the middle of our background. I duplicate the 3 merged James' and set it to Multiply, 50% opacity, then I duplicate it again an set it to Color Burn, opacity 50% [this may vary depending obviously on the image you're using] Next I take 06144A & set it to Exclusion. Then FAE4BE and set it to Luminosity, opacity 10% Then 09949D, set it to Soft Light, opacity 30% Then I added my text. Once I was done that I added my text. Flattened the layer & then duplicated it and set it to Soft Light, 40% opacity. And there you have it. We're done. Other icons made with the same tutorial If you use any of these icons please credit me, ! PLEASE POST YOUR RESULTS! I'd love to see them <333

I'm using Photoshop 7.0 noooow! THE FIRST TUTORIAL!!!!!!!!! ALL RESCOURCES ARE BY ! Screen Opacity 70% Fill 100% Lighten Opacity 70% Fill 100% Lighten Opacity 70% Fill 100% Overlay Opacity 100% Fill 100% At this point I put in my text so that it would have a transparent look without me having to change the opacity And then I re-add my base.. again :P Overlay Opacity 100% Fill 100% Soft Light Opacity 40% Fill 100% And then I add a border <3 Other icons made the same way THE SECOND TUTORIAL!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! ALL RESCOURCES BY Soft Light Opacity 100% Fill 100% Screen Opacity 100% Fill 100% Color Burn Opacity 40% Fill 100% Multiply Opacity 60% Fill 100% And then add your text! :) You might want to throw in a duplicate of your base in there on 'overlay' wherever it looks best, IF you don't like how whispy the icon looks. THE THIRD TUTORIAL!!!!!!!!!!!!!! ALL RESCOURCES BY Exclusion Opacity 100% Fill 100% Color Opacity 40% Fill 100% Overlay Opacity 100% Fill 100% Soft Light Opacity 100% Fill 100% Screen Opacity 30% Fill 100% Then just add your text!! THE FOURTH TUTORIAL!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! - normal - screen - screen - Linear Burn opacity - 50% - overlay opacity 40% - hard light - normal, opacity 30% - lighten - screen Then just add your text & you're done! Please show me what you've done with any of these tutorials! :) I'd love to see what you came up with!

Opacity 100% Fill 100% It looks too whispy for me so I copy my base of Gackt and put it over the the blue layer and set it to Soft Light, Opacity 100% Fill 100% and play around with my color contrast. Now it looks like this left of my base on-- Lighten, Opacity 100% Fill 100% Then I use half of two bases by and slap it on Soft Light Opacity 100% Fill 100% Which will darken it up a bit! Now I just add some text and there we have it!

Going from to I use Photoshot 7.0 <3
All bases are by Gender [unless said otherwise] I start out with my base, two pictures with different sizes, smushed together <3 Lighten, Opacity 60% Fill 100% Multiply, Opacity 100% Fill 100% Lighten, Opacity 100% Fill 100% Multiply, Opacity 100% Fill 70% Lighten, Opacity 40% Fill 100% Screen, Opacity 60% Fill 40% Lighten, Opacity 100% Fill 100% Base made by.... Is this your base? Then I go to Layer >> Flatten Image And paste this thingy~doo by >> And put it on the bottom of my flattened image on Multiply, Opacity 100% Fill 100% Now you can add your text and the such! Here's my end result I'm curious to see your personal results! Hope this tutorial was useful <3

From to In a few steps <3 we start with our base I shrink it down to 200x300, sharpen it once & crop it into my sweet little 100x100 box :) now it looks like this. Then I take this base by (all of 'em are by actually) & put it on Multiply, 100% I use the eraser tool to take off the blotches on his face Opacity: 60%, Fill 40% Opacity: 20% Fill 60% I finish off with a black 1px border, and the word "VANILLA" in Artistamp Medium bold font with decorative text at the bottom. Hope this has been helpful or at least interesting :) lol!
